Name: Legendary Sword
Description: An enchanted sword that can draw out the powers of a warrior. It cannot be used by those aligned with darkness.

Name: Sword of Dark Destruction
Description: A malevolent sword that ups the power of a dark-type being. It can only used by those who have sold their souls to darkness.

Name: Dark Energy
Description: A tainted energy for fiends that makes them powerful. It powers up a dark being by 500 points.

Name: Axe of Despair
Description: A corrupt axe that has the face of a fiend placed on it. It maximizes the power of a fiend, beast warrior, etc.

Name: Laser Cannon Armor
Description: A mechanical suit of armor that is fitted with a laser cannon. If equipped by an insect, etc., it can fire powerful beams.

Name: Insect Armor with Laser Cannon
Description: A mechanical suit of armor that is fitted with a flame thrower. If equipped by an insect, etc., it can shoot intense flames.

Name: Elf's Light
Description: An enchanted light that is cast by benign beings such as fairies. The sacred light powers up an elf, etc., when it is equipped.

Name: Beast Fangs
Description: A viciously arranged set of fangs that can enhance power. It is only useful on a monster with fangs such as a beast.

Name: Steel Shell
Description: A tortoiselike shell that is made out of rugged steel. It powers up only a monster that has a shell to begin with.

Name: Vile Germs
Description: A swarm of giant germs with eyes that was created by fiends. It can be used to power up a forest plant.

Name: Black Pendant
Description: A mystical pendant that features a purplish gemstone. When it is equipped, it powers up a dark magician, etc.

Name: Silver Bow and Arrow
Description: An enchanted set of bow and arrows that is crafted out of silver. When it is equipped, it powers up a fairy, etc.

Name: Horn of Light
Description: A glowing horn that is used to power up a horned being. It has no effect on dark monsters.

Name: Horn of the Unicorn
Description: A spiraling horn that can boost power when it is equipped. It is usable only by a dark monster with a horn on its head.

Name: Dragon Treasure
Description: An enormous crystal that is a legendary treasure among dragons. It is said to be able to power up any dragon.

Name: Electro-Whip
Description: A sharply tipped, electrified whip that stuns the victim. It powers up a designated character such as a female warrior.

Name: Cyber Shield
Description: A piece of body armor that is made exclusively for females. It alters the wearer's personality and powers her up.

Name: Elegant Egotist
Description: A magical kaleidoscope that works with a Harpie Lady. It triples a Harpie Lady into Harpie Lady Sisters.

Name: Mystical Moon
Description: A jaundiced full moon whose rays arouse savage spirits. Its supernatural force powers up a beast, etc.

Name: Stop Defense
Description: A spell card that makes all enemy monsters capable of only attacking on the next turn, and thus not able to defend themselves.

Name: Malevolent Nuzzler
Description: The kiss of a female fiend that darkly empowers the recipient. It works on a female or a dark monster, etc.

Name: Violet Crystal
Description: A beautiful, violet-colored crystal that holds a mystic power. It can power up a chosen monster such as a zombie.

Name: Book of Secret Arts
Description: A magically charged book that powers up a magician, etc. It cannot be read by anyone with evil in their heart.

Name: Invigoration
Description: A blast of energy that can power up a designated monster. It will work on a thunder, rock or pyro monster.

Name: Machine Conversion Factory
Description: A machining factory that converts and modifies all machinery. It can be used to power up a chosen machine.

Name: Raise Body Heat
Description: A spell card that absorbs solar energy to empower a monster. It works on a designated dinosaur, etc.

Name: Follow Wind
Description: A spell card of a wind that empowers a designated monster. It works on a flying monster such as a bird beast.

Name: Power of Kaishin
Description: A spell card of a trident that powers up a monster of the sea. It can be used on an aqua, fish or sea dragon type.

Name: Dragon Capture Jar
Description: An enchanted jar that is irresistible to any kind of dragon. It will suck in every dragon on the opponent's field.

Name: Forest
Description: A spell card that changes the field into a verdant forest. It benefits plants, beast warriors, insects and beasts.

Name: Wasteland
Description: A spell card that changes the field into a desolate wasteland. It benefits the zombies, dinosaurs and rock-type monsters.

Name: Mountain
Description: A spell card that changes the field into a craggy mountain. It benefits dragons, wing beasts and thunder-type monsters.

Name: Sogen
Description: A spell card that changes the field into a grassy meadow. It benefits beast warriors and warriors.

Name: Umi
Description: Transforms the field into a sea. It benefits aqua, thunder and sea dragon types and disadvantages machines and pyro monster

Name: Yami
Description: Transforms the field into darkness. It benefits magicians and fiends, and disadvantages fairies.

Name: Dark Hole
Description: A vortex of darkness that draws in all beings without mercy. It destroys every monster on the field.

Name: Raigeki
Description: An immense thunderbolt that strikes with intense power. It destroys every monster on the foe's field.

Name: Mooyan Curry
Description: A succulent beef curry that boasts a restorative power. It restores the player's LP by 200.

Name: Red Medicine
Description: A medicinal potion that has a fair restorative power. It restores the player's LP by 500.

Name: Goblin's Secret Remedy
Description: A medicine carried by goblins with a restorative power. It restores the player's LP by 1,000.

Name: Soul of the Pure
Description: The blood of a fairy that she collected by injuring herself. It restores the player's LP by 2,000.

Name: Dian Keto the Cure Master
Description: A kindly deity that heals players of any kind of injury. It restores the player's LP by 5,000.

Name: Sparks
Description: An attacking spell card that showers the foe with embers. It inflicts 50LP damage directly on the opponent.

Name: Hinotama
Description: An attacking spell card that strikes the foe with fireballs. It inflicts 100LP damage directly on the opponent.

Name: Final Flame
Description: A spell card that condemns the foe to a burning at the stake. It inflicts 200LP damage directly on the opponent.

Name: Ookazi
Description: A spell card that ignites a huge blaze that burns all day. It inflicts 500LP damage directly on the opponent.

Name: Tremendous Fire
Description: A spell card that ignites an inferno of ferocious intensity. It inflicts 1000LP damage directly on the opponent.

Name: Swords of Revealing Light
Description: A spell that reveals all the foe's monsters over three turns. The opposing monsters are prevented from attacking over that time.

Name: Spellbinding Circle
Description: A magical six-pointed star that lays a debilitating curse. It lowers the power of all opposing monsters on the field.

Name: Dark-Piercing Light
Description: A spell that casts a dazzling blaze of light over the opponent. It reveals every opposing monster on the field.

Name: Destiny Board
Description: "A spectral figure that joins others to bring doom to foes. Victory is automatic if the ""FINAL"" message is completed."

Name: "Spirit Message ""I"""
Description: "A spectral figure that joins others to bring doom to foes. Victory is automatic if the ""FINAL"" message is completed."

Name: "Spirit Message ""N"""
Description: "A spectral figure that joins others to bring doom to foes. Victory is automatic if the ""FINAL"" message is completed."

Name: "Spirit Message ""A"""
Description: "A spectral figure that joins others to bring doom to foes. Victory is automatic if the ""FINAL"" message is completed."

Name: "Spirit Message ""L"""
Description: "A spectral figure that joins others to bring doom to foes. Victory is automatic if the ""FINAL"" message is completed."

Name: Kunai with Chain
Description: A bladed weapon on a chain that is very easy to use. It can be equipped by any warrior to boost attack power.

Name: Magical Labyrinth
Description: An equipment card that only works with a Labyrinth Wall. It strongly enhances the card that equips it.

Name: Warrior Elimination
Description: A spell that exacts a terrible toll on warrior-type beings. On use, it destroys all warriors on the field.

Name: Salamandra
Description: An equipment card that has the power of a wicked fiery monster. It can power up any pyro-type monster.

Name: Cursebreaker
Description: Negates any level-reducing spell used on the player's monsters. It restores the levels of the player's monsters on the field.

Name: Eternal Rest
Description: A spell that brings everlasting peace to all forms of zombies. It destroys all zombies on the opponent's field.

Name: Megamorph
Description: A spell that gigantically transforms a monster on the field. The chosen monster is made much more powerful.

Name: Metalmorph
Description: A card that metalizes certain kinds of monsters on the field. The chosen monster is made into a machine.

Name: Winged Trumpeter
Description: A fairy on a trumpet, whose sweet notes ring clearly far away. It uplifts and powers up a fairy.

Name: Stain Storm
Description: Acid rain caused by air pollution that is ruinous to machines. It destroys all machines on the foe's field.

Name: Crush Card
Description: The scourge of all high-power monsters out on the field. It destroys all enemy monsters with ATK of minimum 1500.

Name: Eradicating Aerosol
Description: An aerosol insecticide that brings instant ruin to bugs. It destroys every insect on the foe's field.

Name: Breath of Light
Description: An ethereal wind whose caress erodes rock types to mere dust. It destroys every rock monster on the foe's field.

Name: Eternal Drought
Description: A spell that leaves the land parched and ruined for all fish. It destroys every fish on the opponent's field.

Name: Curse of Millennium Shield
Description: A ritual for summoning a tough shield in return for a tribute. For this ritual, a One-Eyed Shield Dragon, etc., is needed.

Name: Yamadron Ritual
Description: A ritual for summoning a Yamadron in return for a tribute. For this ritual, a Mountain Warrior, etc., is needed.

Name: Gate Guardian Ritual
Description: A ritual for summoning a Gate Guardian in return for tributes. For this ritual, Sanga, Kazejin, and Suijin are needed.

Name: Bright Castle
Description: A spell book containing a castle that looses a vivid light. The dazzling light powers up a light monster.

Name: Shadow Spell
Description: A spell that weakens all the monsters on the foe's field. Every enemy monster's level is lowered by two.

Name: Black Luster Ritual
Description: A ritual for summoning a Black Luster Soldier with tributes. For this ritual, a Gaia the Fierce Knight, etc., is needed.

Name: Zera Ritual
Description: A ritual for summoning a Zera the Mant in return for a tribute. For this ritual, a Ryu-Kishin Powered, etc., is needed.

Name: Harpie's Feather Duster
Description: A feather duster that is made from a Harpie Lady's feather. It sweeps away all spell and trap cards on the foe's field.

Name: War-Lion Ritual
Description: A ritual for summoning a Super War-Lion in return for tributes. For this ritual, two monsters and a Leogun are needed.

Name: Beastly Mirror Ritual
Description: A ritual for summoning a Fiend's Mirror in return for tributes. For this, two monsters and a Fiend Reflection #1 are needed.

Name: Ultimate Dragon
Description: Summons a Blue-Eyes Ultimate Dragon with tributes. For this ritual, three Blue-Eyes White Dragons are needed.

Name: Commencement Dance
Description: A ritual for summoning a Performance of Sword with a tribute. For this ritual, a Water Omotics, etc., is needed.

Name: Hamburger Recipe
Description: A ritual for summoning a Hungry Burger in return for a tribute. For this ritual, a Bio Plant, etc., is needed.

Name: Revival of Sennen Genjin
Description: A ritual for summoning a Sengenjin in return for tributes. For this, two monsters and a Hitotsu-Me Giant are needed.

Name: Novox's Prayer
Description: A ritual for summoning a Skull Guardian in return for a tribute. For this ritual, an M-Warrior #1, etc., is needed.

Name: Curse of Tri-Horned Dragon
Description: A ritual for summoning a Tri-Horned Dragon with a tribute. For this ritual, a B. Dragon Jungle King, etc., is needed.

Name: House of Adhesive Tape
Description: A trap card that is deadly to low-powered monsters that attack it. If the monster's ATK is 500 or lower, the trap wipes it out.

Name: Eatgaboon
Description: A trap card that is deadly to mid-powered monsters that attack it. If the monster's ATK is 1,000 or less, the trap wipes it out.

Name: Bear Trap
Description: A trap card that is deadly to stronger monsters that attack it. If the monster's ATK is 1,500 or less, the trap wipes it out.

Name: Invisible Wire
Description: A trap card that is deadly to strong monsters that attack it. If the monster's ATK is 2,000 or less, the trap wipes it out.

Name: Acid Trap Hole
Description: A trap card that is deadly to any monster that attacks it. If the monster's ATK is 3,000 or less, the trap wipes it out.

Name: Widespread Ruin
Description: A trap card that is deadly to any monster that attacks it. It explodes as soon as it is attacked, destroying the monster.

Name: Goblin Fan
Description: A trap card that reflects a direct LP attack back at the foe. It works on attack spells like Sparks and Tremendous Fire.

Name: Bad Reaction to Simochi
Description: A trap card that reverses the effect of any healing spell card. If a healing card is used, it injures the user.

Name: Reverse Trap
Description: A trap card that reverses the effect of any power-up card. If a power-up card is used, it cuts power instead.

Name: Fake Trap
Description: A fake trap card that is intended only to fool the opponent. Nothing happens if it is attacked.

Name: Revived Serpent Night Dragon
Description: A ritual for summoning a Serpent Night Dragon with a tribute. For this, a Darkfire Dragon, etc., is needed.

Name: Turtle Oath
Description: A ritual for summoning a Crab Turtle in return for a tribute. This ritual requires a 30,000-Year White Turtle, etc.

Name: Contract of Mask
Description: A ritual for summoning a Mask of Shine & Dark with tributes. For this, two monsters and a Mask of Darkness are needed.

Name: Resurrection of Chakra
Description: A ritual for summoning a Chakra in return for a tribute. For this, a Versago the Destroyer, etc., is needed.

Name: Puppet Ritual
Description: A ritual for summoning a Psycho-Puppet in return for a tribute. For this, a Mysterious Puppeteer, etc., is needed.

Name: Javelin Beetle Pact
Description: A ritual for summoning a Javelin Beetle in return for a tribute. For this ritual, a Hercules Beetle, etc., is needed.

Name: Garma Sword Oath
Description: A ritual for summoning a Garma Sword in return for tributes. For this, two monsters and a Succubus Knight are needed.

Name: Cosmo Queen's Prayer
Description: A ritual for summoning a Cosmo Queen in return for a tribute. For this, a Queen of Autumn Leaves, etc., is needed.

Name: Revival of Dokurorider
Description: A ritual for summoning a Dokurorider in return for tributes. For this, two monsters and a Temple of Skulls are needed.

Name: Fortress Whale's Oath
Description: A ritual for summoning a Fortress Whale with tributes. For this, two monsters and a Mech Bass are needed.

Name: Dark Magic Ritual
Description: Summons a Magician of Black Chaos in return for a tribute. For this, a Dark Magician, etc., is needed.

Name: Brain Control
Description: A spell that can take over a monster on the opponent's field. The affected monster is put under control until the turn ends.

Name: Anti Raigeki
Description: A trap card that protects the player's monsters from Raigeki. Instead, it destroys all the monsters on the foe's field.

Name: Black Illusion Ritual
Description: A ritual for summoning a Relinquished in return for a tribute. For this, a Dark-Eyes Illusionist, etc., is needed.

Name: Change of Heart
Description: A spell that can take over a monster on the opponent's field. The affected monster is put under control.

Name: Multiply
Description: A spell that causes a Kuriboh on the player's field to multiply. The monster and its copies fill the field completely.

Name: Exile of the Wicked
Description: A holy spell that is feared and loathed by every kind of fiend. It causes all fiends on the opponent's field to disappear.

Name: Last Day of Witch
Description: An attack spell that is devastating to any kind of magician. It causes all magicians on the foe's field to disappear.

Name: Restructer Revolution
Description: An attack spell that directly hits the opponent's LP. It inflicts 200LP damage for every card in the foe's hand.

Name: Pot of Greed
Description: A card that allows the player to draw cards from the deck. Up to two cards may be drawn if there is room in the hand.

Name: The Inexperienced Spy
Description: A spell that enables the player to look at the foe's hand. All the cards in the opponent's hand become visible.

Name: Amazon Archers
Description: A trap card of female archers that rain arrows on a foe. It powers down a monster on the foe's field.

Name: Messenger of Peace
Description: A spell cast by a pacifist fairy. It immobilizes all monsters on the foe's field with an ATK of 1,500 or higher for one turn.

Name: Darkness Approaches
Description: A spell that is used to conceal the identity of cards. It makes all cards on the player's field turn facedown.

Name: Final Destiny
Description: A spell that brings total devastation on the entire proceedings. It destroys all cards on the field and in the hands.

Name: Heavy Storm
Description: A spell that totally wipes out every card on the playing field. It creates a storm that blows away all cards on the field.

Name: Monster Reborn
Description: A spell that resurrects a monster from the opponent's graveyard and places it on the player's side of the field.

Name: Gravedigger Ghoul
Description: A spell that brings forth a ghoul that desecrates graves. It carries off all the monsters in graveyards.

Name: Torrential Tribute
Description: A trap card that has dire consequences to anyone that trips it. If attacked, it destroys all monsters on the foe's field.

Name: Beckon to Darkness
Description: A trap card that causes the banishment of a monster to darkness. If attacked, it destroys a monster on the foe's field.

Name: Infinite Dismissal
Description: A trap card that causes immobilization when it is tripped. The attacker is immobilized for one turn.

Name: 7 Completed
Description: An equip spell that is designed to power up a machine. It is only intended to power up a Slot Machine.
